@Euridion "Maybe they are just using a data compression technique that are far better than anyone else is using?"

Yify encodes are not better than any good encoder group.

No good encoders waste their time doing high resolution, low bit rate encodes because they know you get better results by going to a lower resolution. 

Case in point. 
I did my own encode of Batman Begins to compare with YIFY.
No special tuning at all, just defaults, single pass Q22.

Mine is labled m, YIFY labled Y.

http://imageshack.us/a/img411/7189/mbbcrop.png
http://imageshack.us/a/img42/3271/ybbcrop.png

(if links don't work, copy paste to a separate window).

Look at his face, his hair and the texture on the seat  behind him. It is all better in my encode, despite it being smaller in size and lower resolution.

It is better BECAUSE it is lower resolution.  Going to low bit rates on higher resolution smears away details and increases artifacts.

YIFY encodes would be better if he kept the same bit rate and dropped his resolution.

@CosmAvngr
You're absolutely right. I used to devote myself only to YIFY's torrents b/c I watched these on my laptop, but when I finally decided to put them on the big screen, I was appalled by the results. This degree of compression is counterproductive.

@CosmAvngr
The rips are fine for the size. I watch on 42" LCD and it looks great. You can't compare half a frame of an entire movie and conclude that YIFY's rips in general are no better than SD rips. That's ludicrous.

The only thing YIFY could improve would be to give the same bitrate for longer movies instead of keeping the same size. That's probably the case with Batman Begins which is runs at 2h:20min (YIFY's rip@850MB=6,1MB/min), this movie is 1h:43 mins, YIFY's rip 700MB=6,8MB/min that's more than 10% bitrate... 

Get YIFY's 1080p rips under 2GB if 720p under 800MB is not good for you.

@Manuel

I DL YIFY encodes of movies I don't care that much about. So I have seen a fair number of them, and all of them have been fairly mediocre with often with visible artifacts. Rock of Ages and Prometheus both had annoying artifacts in them recently.

For movies I really like, like Batman Begins I get a real decent encode, I have an 8GB release of that with multi-channel sound. 

The comparison above is representative and matters because I was finding that my personal HDTV 540p encodes I do from WTV files look better than YIFY 720p encodes.

So I re-encoded BB in 540p, to smaller size than YIFY BB, and it was more detailed and looked better. That is with no special tuning or anything.

I really can't believe so many people don't realize that going to smaller resolution is a better solution for low bit rate encodes, they come out with more detail and less artifacts. 

They just see 720p and small size. Sure it is technically 720p, but it is more smeared than if it was 540p encode at the same bit rate.

@CosmAvngr

I think x264 works much better at higher resolutions, I'll take YIFY's 720p encodes any time over same sized 540p rips.
In general the picture will look much sharper and detailed than the 540p resized on the LCD which will look blurry. Watching really closely on your PC you might find a scene or two where the 540p might look more detailed in a spot.
But I agree if you really like a movie you should buy the Bluray or get a 1080p >4GB rip if you can't afford it.
